# AI Car Game – Development Plan

Goal:
Build a 2D car racing environment for reinforcement learning.

The system will start as a playable pygame game and evolve into a gym-style RL environment.

---

# Milestone 1 – Playable Game

Files:
- track.py
- car.py
- main.py

Features:
- Load track image
- White = road, black = wall
- Car rectangle that moves with WASD
- Basic physics (speed, steering)
- Collision with walls
- Window renders track and car
- Start / finish line detection
- Checkpoint detection and zone grouping
- Lap validation (all checkpoints required before finish counts)
- Lap counting
- Lap timers
- Fastest lap tracking
- Race completion after 3 valid laps
- Finish screen with race results

Definition of done:
Running `python main.py` allows the user to drive the car around, complete valid laps, and finish a 3-lap race with results shown.

---

# Milestone 2 – Sensors

Add ray sensors to detect distance to walls.

Files modified:
- track.py
- car.py
- main.py

Features:
- Raycast function
- 7 sensors in front of car
- Debug visualization of rays

Definition of done:
Sensors return normalized distance values.

